  "prompt": "Do love marriages work in India?",
  "response": "Love marriages in India have become increasingly common and accepted, especially in urban areas. Their success depends on various factors:\n\nPros of Love Marriages:\n1. Partners choose each other based on mutual understanding\n2. Often have stronger emotional connection\n3. More likely to share similar interests and values\n4. Generally more open communication\n5. Younger generations are more supportive\n\nChallenges:\n1. Potential family disapproval\n2. Caste and cultural differences\n3. Social pressure and societal judgment\n4. Less family involvement in initial stages\n5. Higher expectations compared to arranged marriages\n\nSuccess Rate:\n- Statistics show love marriages have a similar divorce rate to arranged marriages\n- Success depends on mutual respect, understanding, and commitment\n- Urban and educated couples tend to have more successful love marriages\n\nChanging Trends:\n- Increasing acceptance across different social classes\n- More inter-caste and inter-religious marriages\n- Growing support from younger generations\n- Greater emphasis on individual choice\n\nWhile challenges exist, many love marriages in India are successful, with couples navigating cultural complexities and building strong relationships.\n\nUltimately, the success of a marriage depends on individual commitment, compatibility, and mutual understanding, regardless of how the marriage is arranged.",
